cs.MA, cs.GT, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.AI

The paper deals with a control problem for a population of agents, which suggests that it could belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) category. The use of well quasi orders and the max-flow min-cut theorem suggests that it could also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) categories, respectively. The paper also makes use of regular cost functions, which could place it in the Data Structures (cs.DS) category. Finally, the stochastic nature of the problem and the use of Markov decision processes suggest that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category.
